==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Xanthoprotein
<hw>Xan`tho*pro"te*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xantho-</ets> + <ets>protein</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow acid substance formed by the action of hot
nitric acid on albuminous or proteid matter. It is changed to a deep
orange-yellow color by the addition of ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthopuccine</ent>⟦br⟧
